author: @beckettman42
text: Does anybody know if it is possible to run the API from a local machine.  I have an Ubuntu machine with tensorflow-GPU and google cloud installed.    I have created a project in google cloud, generated a key and enabled vision but I get "Could not automatically determine credentials."    Is what I'm trying to do possible or am I making a stupid error?  I answered my own question by actually reading the link that comes with the error.  :p  Follow the instructions the instructions in the above video until you have input the path for the key and then:  Install Google Cloud SDK on your machine: https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/quickstart-debian-ubuntu  Run 'gcloud auth application-default login' in a terminal and a browser window will come up asking you to sign your life away to google-ai.  Then your machine should be authorized to use the API.   Great Video and happy computing.
